    "body": "It's quite a standard behavior. You can read about here:\r\niOS\r\nhttps://developer.apple.com/ios/human-interface-guidelines/controls/refresh-content-controls/\r\nAndroid\r\nhttps://material.io/guidelines/patterns/swipe-to-refresh.html#\r\n\r\nI believe a user should allow updating the whole screen not only part with assets.\r\n![wallet reload](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6559881/36035855-7c30099a-0db8-11e8-9e0c-811640270770.pn\r\n\r\n## Known bugs\r\n\r\n### 1.Scrolling through main actions area is not a correct behavior.\r\n![img_2759](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6559881/36035962-cc179cb6-0db8-11e8-8e24-5ed471314e35.PNG)\r\n\r\n## 2.Assets auto update on tapping wallet tab in the tab bar should be removed.\r\n![img_2791](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6559881/36158669-29b91666-10dd-11e8-82bb-a1e942dfd232.jpg)\r\n\r\n \r\n",
